.TH XIL\-PARSE "1" "2026\-04\-19" "xil\-pipeline 0.1.8" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xil\-parse
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xil\-parse
[-h] [--episode EPISODE | --tag TAG] [--show SHOW] [--output OUTPUT] [--preview PREVIEW] [--quiet] [--debug] [--stats] [--speakers SPEAKERS] script
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse production script markdown into structured JSON

.TP
\fBscript\fR
Path to the production script markdown file

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-episode\fR \fI\,EPISODE\/\fR
Episode tag (e.g. S01E01) — validates header and auto\-generates absent
cast/sfx configs

.TP
\fB\-\-tag\fR \fI\,TAG\/\fR
Raw tag for non\-episodic content (e.g. V01C03, D01, CH003) — skips
season/episode header validation

.TP
\fB\-\-show\fR \fI\,SHOW\/\fR
Show name override (default: from project.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI\,OUTPUT\/\fR, \fB\-o\fR \fI\,OUTPUT\/\fR
Output JSON path (default: parsed/parsed_<slug>_<TAG>.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-preview\fR \fI\,PREVIEW\/\fR
Show first N dialogue lines (default: show all)

.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR
Only output JSON, skip summary/preview

.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
Write diagnostic CSV alongside JSON output

.TP
\fB\-\-stats\fR
Print per\-speaker dialogue distribution (lines, words, chars, %)

.TP
\fB\-\-speakers\fR \fI\,SPEAKERS\/\fR
Path to speakers.json (default: auto\-detect from CWD, then built\-in)

